<title>USA: Smedvig to buy Scientific.</title>
<headline>Smedvig to buy Scientific.</headline>
<dateline>DENVER 1996-09-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Scientific Software-Intercomp Inc (SSI) said on Wednesday it had signed a letter of intent for substantially all of its assets to be bought by Norway's Smedvig A/S for $23 million and assumption of debt.</p>
<p>Smedvig would assume the current liabilities of SSI, with SSI satisfying its long-term debt liabilities to Lindner Funds, Renaissance Capital Partners and Banc One Corp for about $7 million and the SSI preferred stock from the proceeds of the sale.</p>
<p>SSI will also be responsible for the pending settlement of a class action lawsuit, which is to be substantially funded from the proceeds of insurance.</p>
<p>Preliminary terms for the sale have been approved by SSI's Board of Directors. Closing is expected at year-end.</p>
<p>-- New York newsroom, (212) 859-1610</p>
